# RAG-Based Customer Support Assistant using LangGraph & HITL

This project is part of my VTU internship evaluation. It implements a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) based **Customer Support Assistant** that answers user queries from a PDF knowledge base using a vector database (ChromaDB) and a graph-based workflow (LangGraph) with Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) escalation.[cite:2][cite:8][web:16][web:20]

---

## 1. Features

- PDF-based knowledge base (e.g., `sample_kb.pdf`).
- RAG pipeline: load PDF ‚Üí chunk ‚Üí embed ‚Üí store in ChromaDB ‚Üí retrieve relevant chunks ‚Üí generate answer with LLM.[cite:2][web:16][web:20][web:22]
- Graph-based workflow using LangGraph (2-node flow: process node and output node).
- Intent and confidence based conditional routing.
- Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) escalation for low-confidence or sensitive queries.

